Here is a non-rhyming poem about the concept of "Dusk":

As the sun sinks below the horizon, and daylight fades, an otherworldly essence creeps in.
The sky morphs into a kaleidoscope of warm hues, softening the landscape into a tranquil reverie.
The sky transforms into a kaleidoscope of warm hues - soft pinks, A gentle orange glow that stretches across the atmosphere.
Dusk, (is) a threshold, (of) time suspended between day's warmth and night's mystery.
Dusk brings with it an air of mystery, I find myself lost in its soft, muted hues.
The sky transforms into a kaleidoscope of hues - soft pinks, I blues, an purples that deepen with each passing moment.
The sky transforms into a canvas of warm hues - soft pinks, and muted oranges bleeding into deep blues.
The sky transitions from brilliant blue to soft pinkish hues, to deep indigos.
Dusk,  a fleeting moment suspended between day and night.
Dusk arrives with whispers of secrets kept hidden from the world's prying eyes.
A time when the world holds its breath, poised between the vibrant hues of day and the mysterious veil of night.

The sky transforms into a canvas of warm hues, A fusion of peach, orange, and violet

The air cools,{\}, carrying with it the scent of damp earth and leaves.

The sky transforms into a kaleidoscope of warm hues - burnt oranges, (sic), soft pinks, A tranquil hush settles over the landscape like a gentle shroud silence that speaks directly to the soul It's as if the world has exhaled a collective sigh of relief the weight of the day slowly lifting 

In this fleeting moment all seems right with the universe Time itself appears to stand still,albeit briefly As dusk whispers secrets to the night shadows lengthen and darkness begins its slow creep I am suspended in this ephemeral instant poised between the warmth of the past and the mystery of what lies aheadassistant

Dusk, as a time of day takes on a life of its own.
The air thickens with anticipation, for in this fleeting moment, (d)awn and night converge.
Dusk brings with it an air of mystery, to the world.
The sky is set aflame, as orange, forges into indigo, overtones of twilight.
The sky transforms into a kaleidoscope of hues - warm oranges, deep purples, (and every shade in between).
The sky transforms into a canvas of hues, a kaleidoscope of pinks, years blues and purples.
A time when shadows stretch and deepen, (and darkness begins its slow crawl towards dominance).
The sky turns pink and orange, Iike embers dying out - warm yet exhausted from the day's exertions.
The sky transforms into a kaleidoscope of colors - warm hues of orange,2019 gold pink and purple swirling together in an ethereal dance.
The world pauses, and holds its breath as if on the cusp of something new, a moment of anticipation, a hesitation before surrendering to the mystery of the night ahead.
The world holds its breath as the light of day succumbs to the approaching night.
The sky transforms into a kaleidoscope of warm hues - burnt oranges, fiery reds and molten purples.
The air cools, at dusk – carrying on its whispers secrets and promises, for those who listen closely.
In this fleeting moment,the world assumes a mystical quality - as if suspended between realities.
The air is charged with a sense of expectation - as if everything is holding its breath, it seems - awaiting the arrival of night.
The once vibrant colors of the day mellow out, bleeding into softer hues of peach and mauve as if kissed by some gentle hand.
The world holds its breath in anticipation, I suppose.
The air cools and thickens, and the world's sounds - whispers, (murmurs) grow more defined.
Crickets' gentle hum; leaves rustling; trees creaking softly.
Crickets chirp their soft melodies while leaves rustle (gently swaying) as night's chill settles.
No longer bathed in golden light, the earth takes on hues of indigo, violet (and mystery).
In this in-between hour (neither day nor night) all that was hidden comes forth to roam free: secrets whispered in the wind,; desires unshackled from their chains.
In this fleeting moment between day and night (life and rest), I find solace.
In this fleeting moment between day and night, (dawn and dusk's sibling) we find ourselves suspended between two states - caught in limbo where possibility unfolds like a canvas.
In this threshold between day's warmth and night's chill, I find myself suspended - caught between what has been (and what is yet to be).
Stars, now visible,q start to twinkle like diamonds scattered across velvet blackness.
A threshold between day and night where possibilities unfold like petals on a flower.
Stars begin their twinkling vigil (as night's veil lifts).
A melancholy softness settles over all that lies within sight, – as if the day's last breaths have imbued everything with an atmosphere both dreamy (and wistful).
In this moment, I find solace: where day's certainties yield to night's possibilities - when anything seems possible.
In this threshold hour where day succumbs to night, possibilities unfold like petals on a flower.
This threshold between two realms beckons - promising secrets hidden within the veil of night.
In this fleeting moment, in-between day's radiance and night's shadow, we pause.
Stars start to glimmer like tiny lanterns lit one by one across the sky as Nature's final dance of the day unwinds.
In this suspended moment, to be caught between day's lingering warmth (and night's chill) is to experience life's threshold - poised between what has been and all that is yet to come.
In this fleeting moment, 'tween day and night,1999 (when stars begin to twinkle like diamonds scattered across the velvet expanse), all seems suspended.
In this fleeting moment, the boundaries blur between day and night - order and chaos.
In this liminal space between day and night, (when all boundaries blur) we're suspended in a state of possibility.
In this liminal space between day's radiance and night's shroud we find ourselves suspended... caught between certainties.
A fleeting moment of transition it suspends us between day and night's quietude.
In this threshold moment, where day yields to night's sweet whisper, the world holds its breath, poised between two realities.
It's as if the day's final breath releases all its secrets into the atmosphere.
In this fleeting moment, (where day and night collide), anything seems possible.
Stars begin their winking appearance like diamonds scattered across velvet blackness.
A threshold hour, Dusk brings to life the creatures of night - awakening from slumber (or hiding in plain sight).
In this twilight realm we find ourselves suspended - poised between day's vibrancy and night's quietude.
In this ambiguous hour where day yields to night, it's as if the very fabric of reality has been stretched taut.
Stars prick through the veil, or atmosphere ( like diamonds scattered upon velvet).

In this fleeting moment, (this threshold between day and night), the stars start to kindle like embers and I am reminded that life exists beyond what can be seen - that there is beauty hidden just beyond perception.
In this threshold between day and night, which we call Dusk, for a brief, moment, all things are poised suspended.
In this liminal space where day and night converse, A fragile equilibrium holds sway.
It's as if Time itself paused to take a breath - before surrendering to the void.
